I"ª<h1 id="1-preparation">1. Preparation</h1>
<ul>
  <li>A. Know 3-4 times as much as you will communicate</li>
  <li>B. Have a point</li>
  <li>C. Have multiple stories at hand to illustrate your point</li>
  <li>D. Sit for 30 minutes with your eyes closed before speaking and organize your ideas around a problem</li>
</ul>

<h1 id="2-the-talk-itself">2. The talk itself</h1>
<ul>
  <li>A. Talk about what you know</li>
  <li>B. Use stories from personal experience</li>
  <li>C. Talk to one individual at once</li>
  <li>D. Every fact you share must be given for a clear purpose</li>
  <li>E. The talk should be an unplotted exploration of a set of ideas</li>
  <li>F. Donâ€™t rely on notes or a predetermined structure</li>
  <li>G. Recognize that there is a high probability of failure</li>
  <li>H. Relate the talk to work you have been doing over time</li>
  <li>I. Have a very difficult problem to attempt to grapple with</li>
</ul>
